# examples/kali-llm-lab/hand-walk/Containerfile — reproduce the Kali blog's
# environment so you can walk "Kali & LLM: local with Ollama & 5ire" BY HAND.
#
#   Upstream post : ../upstream-tutorial/  (byte-exact archive + provenance)
#   Canonical URL : https://www.kali.org/blog/kali-llm-ollama-5ire/
#   What it shows : run a local LLM on Kali with Ollama, expose Kali's tools to
#                   the model via mcp-kali-server (the agentic payoff), and chat
#                   from a GUI (5ire).
#
# This is the HAND-WALK sandbox (TODO #3): a **Kali** box for the *server side* —
# Ollama (CPU) + mcp-kali-server, headless. Per the scoping decision this is
# **CPU-only** (no NVIDIA driver) and **server-only** (the 5ire desktop GUI is the
# client — see the sibling ../../kali-llm-desktop-lab/ for the real-5ire VM).
#
# ── AUTHORED, YOU BUILD (not built in this sandbox) ──────────────────────────
# Two reasons, both flagged honestly: (1) the Kali base + an LLM model are a
# multi-GB pull; (2) the post installs Ollama by fetching + executing a prebuilt
# binary from ollama.com — which is your machine's call to trust (the same posture
# as this repo's toolchain-fetch gate; the post even sha512-verifies it, and so
# does RUNBOOK §1). So the Ollama install + model pull live in RUNBOOK.md as steps
# you run, not baked here. The repo's AUTOMATED, verified counterpart is the
# Phase-4 pod ../kali-llm-lab.toml (Ollama + Open WebUI) — use that if you just
# want it working.
#
# Build + run (on your machine):
#   phase4-podman/lab-podman.sh build --tag kali-llm-handwalk \
#       --context examples/kali-llm-lab/hand-walk
#   podman run --rm -it -p 11434:11434 kali-llm-handwalk bash   # then RUNBOOK.md

# ── Base — Kali (the post is written for Kali; this is its environment).
ARG BASE=docker.io/kalilinux/kali-rolling
FROM ${BASE}

ENV DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive

# ── The post's CPU/server prerequisites we CAN bake (apt, from Kali's repos):
#   curl ca-certificates xz-utils zstd → fetch + unpack the Ollama tarball (§1)
#   procps                            → ps/free, for poking at the running server
# NOTE: nvidia-driver/nvidia-smi from the post are deliberately OMITTED (CPU-only).
# mcp-kali-server + the tool metapackages are LARGE; install them per RUNBOOK §4
# so this image stays lean and the heavy pull is an explicit choice.
RUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \
        curl ca-certificates xz-utils zstd procps \
 && rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*

WORKDIR /root
CMD ["bash"]
